ssuming that Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is a Paramahamsa on Vimalananda's scal=
e. You are concluding that Ramakrishna is a Paramahamsa; Abhedananda, Vivek=
ananda etc are lower than that; Vimalananda is a rishi; and hence Vimalanan=
da is superior to Abhedananda and Vivekananda by 2pwr16 to 2. 
=C2=A0 
Is P=
aramahamsa Nithyananda, who was caught in a sex scandal, also a Paramahamsa=
 because he is known so? See, how people are famously known may or may not =
reflect their spiritual stature. Real spiritual stature is internal and you=
 cannot see it. 
=C2=A0 
We do not know who Ramakrishna Paramahamsa really =
is. He may not be just a paramahamsa on Vimalananda's scale, but be a siddh=
a or a natha or even a rishi. He may even be Vishnu himself, as he himself =
said and some religious experts of that time declared based on various sign=
s. If Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is Vishnu himself, Vivekananda, Abhedananda e=
tc can definitely be rishis or naths in Vimalananda's scale. If your argume=
nt is that they cannot be because they did not demonstrate siddhis compatib=
le with that status, that is a non-point as I explained above. The disagree=
ment between then boils down a difference in the relevance and importance o=
